 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "Full Actors-pattern implementation (Governor + MarketEntry-LLM mock advisor + langgraph-clj StateGraph + append-only audit ledger + MemStore/DatomicStore via langchain-store.core), adapted from the cloud-itonami-iso3166-ago reference implementation and the same-OHADA-framework siblings cloud-itonami-iso3166-dji/-mli: src/marketentry/{facts,governor,registry,store,marketentryllm,operation,phase}.cljc + full test suite (governor contract, store contract MemStore≡DatomicStore parity, registry pure-function, phase, facts) + docs/business-model.md + docs/operator-guide.md. The jurisdiction dossier (marketentry.facts) is intentionally THINNER and more conservative than sibling jurisdictions (e.g. AGO/MLI): research found no independently-verifiable Portuguese official name for the national procurement regulatory body, no verified national e-procurement portal, and no distinct tax-ID scheme for Guinea-Bissau, so :owner-authority/:national-spec say so honestly rather than inventing either, the governor is SIX checks (not AGO's seven -- no analog of AGO's nif-unverified/MLI's nif-unverified check, mirroring cloud-itonami-iso3166-stp/-sdn precedent), and the demo engagement set is 5 engagements. This also corrects this repo's original scaffold, which claimed an unverifiable named regulator (\"ARMP\") for Guinea-Bissau specifically -- that claim has been removed from facts.cljc, organization.edn, README.md and docs/ and replaced with only what is independently verified: Lei-Quadro Relativo Aos Contratos Públicos (procurement legal basis, PPIAF-indexed) and Conservatória do Registo Comercial / Centro de Formalização de Empresas (commercial registration authority, OHADA framework)."}
